  e.push(['natl-res','resources','national','National Disability Resources Directory','NATIONAL DISABILITY & EDUCATION RESOURCES\n\nIDEA — Parents & Families\n(U.S. Dept. of Education) [Law & SpEd Guidance]\n  Official federal resource explaining parent rights under IDEA. Links families to federally funded Parent Training & Information Centers (PTIs) in every state. OSEP funds projects providing free inform\n  Services: PTI/CPRC directory for every state, DC, PR, USVI, Pacific entities; IDEA topic-area resources; early learning resources; ECTA Center family resources; military-connected children resources; OCR civil \n  Cost: Free\n\nCenter for Parent Information & Resources (CPIR)\n(parentcenterhub.org) [Law & SpEd Guidance]\n  Central hub serving the national network of Parent Centers. Provides curated information, training materials, and resources to PTIs and CPRCs so they can serve families. Library of 1,100+ family-frien\n  Services: Resource library searchable by topic (1,100+ items); \'New to Disability?\' starting guides; IDEA training materials; OSEP glossaries (Spanish, Korean); parent participation guides for Early Interventio\n  Cost: Free\n\nCouncil of Parent Attorneys & Advocates (COPAA) [Law & SpEd Guidance]\n  Independent nonprofit protecting civil rights of students with disabilities. Files amicus briefs and lawsuits in systemic cases of national significance. Provides online training for parents, advocate\n  Services: Online training courses (SEAT certification program); weekly/monthly/quarterly roundtables by membership category; on-demand webinar library; attorney/advocate member directory; career center; Navigat\n  Cost: Membership-based (tiered): Parent memberships available; some resources free to registered guests. 501(c)(3).\n\nParent to Parent USA (P2P USA) [Peer Support]\n  National nonprofit supporting a network of Parent to Parent programs in all 50 states. Facilitates intentional one-to-one matches between trained volunteer Support Pare